I just heard something that was brilliant, “Meditation with your phone is like having an AA meeting in a bar” 

I can’t agree more. Don’t get me wrong, there are some good apps to help you get started, but in the end, I believe it’s important to be able to completely disconnect and be alone with your thoughts. 

🧘‍♀️Meditation is powerful in all forms and most people don’t do it. 

This is coming from a gal that used to blast Metallica to drown out my thoughts just so I could get a break. But honestly, there is something so powerful about putting your phone away and just being 100% present with and for yourself. 

It takes, time, patients, and practice, try it! If it doesn’t work, ask yourself why. Get to the bottom of what’s challenging you and continue to work thought it as you take deep breaths. You might be surprised at how amazing you feel.

Random post today, but do you know your personality type? 
For years I thought I was just weird and often felt misunderstood. 

It wasn't until a total stranger came up to me at a mastermind group I was invited to attend and said “you know you are an introvert right?” (@jameswedmore- that was you at @lewishowes mastermind a million years ago!)
I had no idea what to think of it. He said “You should do a personality test”. 

I had no idea what to think! It takes one to know one and he clearly saw my struggle as I was awkwardly and unintentionally pulling away from the group. 

Learning about my personality helped me understand myself and things I thought were flaws. 

I'm an introvert, INTJ to be exact, and although I can rock a stage with total confidence in front of thousands of people, it's hard for me to to open up to people one on one. 
Being an introvert doesn't mean you are shy or don't like people.

INTJ's are analytical thinkers who prefer to work independently and are often focused on long-term goals. We are known for our strategic planning abilities, logical reasoning, and visionary thinking. 
We don't trust easily but when we do it is deep and meaningful. 

Many people misunderstand others because they don't know the different personality types. Don't judge, learn! Not just about others but about yourself. 
#introvert #intjfemale

Hey there! Did you know that getting enough sleep is crucial for weight loss and hormone balance? 🌙

I've never been a great sleeper, but as I've gotten older I've REALLY had to prioritize sleep.  Netflix is NOT worth it when it's sacrificing your health and fat loss goals, and trust me it is. 

When you're sleep deprived, your body produces more of the hormone ghrelin which stimulates hunger and decreases the hormone leptin which helps you feel full. This means you're more likely to overeat and make poor food choices. 😴🍔

Lack of sleep also affects your body's ability to regulate insulin, which can lead to weight gain and even insulin resistance over time. 😔

So, if you're trying to lose weight or balance your hormones, make sure to prioritize getting 7-9 hours of quality sleep each night. Your body and mind will thank you! ❤️

 #sleep #sleepwell #SleepBetter #sleepingbeauty #sleeptips #sleeping #hormonesupport #hormonesmatter #hormonesbalance

I turned 50 this month and I have never felt happier, healthier, and at peace with my life. 

With that said, it’s weird turning 50! I remember my parents turning 50 and it sounding so old, yet here I am feeling like I’m just really getting settle into this crazy little life. 

The best part of being 50....
🙌I’m more confident in my own skin and proud of my accomplishments yet still hungry to learn everyday. 

😀I care less about making everyone happy and more about doing what makes me happy which makes life so much easier. 

⚖️I’ve found balance in living a healthy lifestyle and letting go of chasing perfection. 

🤪I learned to love my curves, freckles, dimples, and quirks that make me unique. 

😉I’ve embraced my introverted personality and speak up when I need time alone to recharge. 

💪I’ve accept that I can’t fix the world, but I can help those that want to learn how to get healthy. 

Cheers to the next 50 being as amazing as the first 50…and yes, I play on making it to 100! Thank you for being a part of my journey! 🍾

I gained 7lbs on a two week vacation😳🙈😳🙈😳🙈😳🙈😳🙈😳
Truth bomb, I felt so yucky on the last half of the trip. I knew I gained a few pounds but was a bit surprised when I got home and weighed myself. 

⚖️I’m not big on the scale, but like to check in on my smart scale now and again. 7lbs on my tiny 5’3 frame is a lot and pushes me into the “tight clothes” category. 😩

We eat very healthy on vacations, with a few extra treats (There should be an emoji for Huckleberry shakes, omg worth it) so I knew it wasn’t fat gain. 

The much younger me would have freaked out and gone on a crazy diet. But i knew it wasn’t from over eating. It was from being so sedentary!

🧘‍♀️Sitting in the car, sitting on a boat, sitting at the lake, sitting at the fire, good lord, all i did was sit on my butt! etc! 

Relaxing is one thing, but wow did it show the power of movement on the lymphatic system! 

🏋️Working out is so much more than “burning calories”- fyi calories are load of crap (more on that later)

🛜We have a fascinating network keeping our bodies healthy; it’s called the lymphatic system. Unlike the heart, it doesn’t have its own pump, your movement is the pump! 
Here’s a brief overview of the lymph system:

💧Lymph, a clear fluid, flows through this system, collecting toxins, waste, and pathogens from our tissues. It acts as a vital defender against infections! 🛡️

💪 Exercise, dry brushing, and deep breathing can boost lymphatic flow, keeping it running smoothly like a well-oiled machine! 🏃‍♀️

🌿 So, let's get moving and support our lymphatic system to stay vibrant, healthy, and ready to defend us (and spare us the unnecessary lbs on the scale😬)! 
 #LymphaticSystem #HealthAndWellness 
#StayActive 
#ImmuneBoost

Let’s reintroduce SELF-CARE because it’s so much more than slapping on a mud mask or jumping in an ice bath for a post. 

Self-care is protecting your ENERGY in a way that helps YOU thrive. 

✅Personal Boundaries: Not giving everyone 24/7 access to you, not letting negative people in your close circle, and saying NO to things you say yes to out of guilt. 

✅Curated Content: Unfollowing or muting accounts that don’t make you feel good for whatever reason. Deleting time-sucking apps that don’t align with your goals and intentions

✅Information anti-overload: Being mindful of the news and content you consume in the news, articles, podcasts, shows, etc. Be informed, but not bombarded can have an emotional and mental impact on your health especially if you are in empath. 

✅Energy accounting: Be aware of what people and activities charge you and drain you. Allow for extra time to rest and recover after positive activities and events that are draining. 

✅Anti-goal elimination: Knowing what isn’t aligned with your goals is as powerful as knowing your goals. This allows you to avoid situations and eliminate activities that don’t jive with your well-being. 

✅Environmental Respect: Your environment can greatly impact your mood and productivity. Allow yourself a self-respecting space that empowers your mood and productivity to reach new levels. 

✅Financial balance: Automate savings, even if it’s small. Check accounts regularly and plan ahead. Allow yourself to prioritize your health over materialistic items. 

Thoughts, what do you do for self-care?
